<h2 class="bac">Summary:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong A&ndash;level grades and a minimum 2:1 degree (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>Primary locations: Opportunities in London, Bromley &#38; Chester (all in the UK)</li>
	<li>3&ndash;year programme</li>
	<li>Opportunity to study for IAQ, CIMA or CFA</li>
	<li>Online application form</li>
	<li>Application Deadline: 12 November 2010</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Markets Operations/Middle Office Group (GMO&#38;MO) provides controlled and cost&ndash;effective post&ndash;trade processes in support of our Capital Markets, Corporate Investments, Corporate Treasury, Global Wealth and Investment Management businesses. 
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Middle Office </H3>
<p class="bac">
This group within GMO&#38;MO delivers control functions responsible for providing assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results, in support of Global Markets, Corporate Treasury and Corporate Investments businesses. There are seven core GMO functions that are critical in ensuring business process control: new business development, trade capture substantiation, P&#38;L validation, risk/position validation, balance sheet substantiation, event monitoring and front&ndash;back process oversight. 
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Global Markets Operations</H3>
<p class="bac">
Some of the core processes in this group include confirmations, client services and on&ndash;boarding, trades processing, settlements and custody and asset servicing. With approximately 20 million transactions per day, the organisational infrastructure is designed to ensure global consistency of processes and strong global and local supervision.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
As an Analyst in GMO&#38;MO, you&#39;ll:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Join a three&ndash;year programme that aims to develop exceptional analysts </li> 
	<li>Work in an environment that promotes innate talent in the people we hire, and equips them with skills to complement that talent</li>
	<li>Spend the first year of the programme developing your business, financial and analytical skills through on&ndash;the&ndash;job training, mentoring and classroom sessions</li>
	<li>Spend your second and third years using these newly acquired skills and knowledge to cement your performance in your role and team </li>
	<li>Study for IAQ, CIMA or CFA in your second and third years, subject to satisfactory performance</li>
	<li>Undergo Six Sigma training to attain the Green Belt accreditation</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Strong academic qualifications are important, but you&#39;ll also need to demonstrate drive, innovation and dedication to a career in Middle Office or Global Operations.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
We accept applications from a diverse range of degree disciplines, although maths, accounting and finance subjects are key for this line of business. In addition, teamwork, leadership and problem&ndash;solving skills, plus creativity, are important, as is the ability to work in a fast&ndash;paced environment, multi&ndash;task and interact with a variety of people. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The programme begins with intensive sessions to help you develop the business, financial and analytical skills needed to hit the ground running. After formal training, you will take on real responsibility in an assigned role, working with – and learning from – teams of professionals, including senior experts in their area, as well as colleagues from around the globe. There will be opportunities to collaborate on exciting projects that contribute to business success and next&ndash;generation advances, while developing a network of contacts. During the programme, there will be opportunities to rotate to different groups, depending on business requirements and your own development needs. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

